videos.text:
Garage transformation tutorial ✨
Step by step instructions;

Here’s how we transformed this old concrete garage into a chic Scandi Inspired building.

1) Remove old Wooden panelling from the front.
2) Adjust the wooden frame to suit the panels (ours wasn’t straight, so we straightened this up.
3) Pre drill Holes through the concrete and Screw the 2x1 slats from the inside of the garage.
4) Attach corner piece to the side and front.
5) Cut Panels to size, they simply hook on to each other, and then you screw the opposite side. Continue the the end. 
6) Add either another corner piece or J piece to finish.
7) On the the front. The corner pieces were on the outside of the walls. We then lined around the Door with the J pieces.
8) we then cut the panels to pop them i between the corner and J piece and continued over the top.
9) for the roof we had a J piece at one end and the other side was against the fascia board. We repeated the same process as the side but with out the corner panels. 

It’s that easy, any questions? Just ask! 

Don’t forget to Save for later !! 

Full Cost Breakdown

22 Honey Oak - Vox Fronto Slat Wall £830 

3 Vox Fronto Outside Corner Trim £90

4 Vox Fronto J Trim  £51

Wooden battens and screws
£60

Total 🟰 1031.40

videos.text:
day 3 of my DREAM garage makeover! Today I did more painting. I wasn’t just going to leave the black paint looks totally crazy.. don’t worry 😆 I taped off the lower 18 inches and then rolled the entire wall with a light gray called Tundra by @sherwinwilliams. 
I decided to add a little more black and totally color drenched the entire back corner where our hot water heater is to trick my brain into thinking it doesn’t exist. 
Next up… flooring!!! I debated between epoxy or floor tiles.. what do you think I picked? #garagemakeover #budgetmakeover #diy #doityourself #buildergradeupgrade #paintwithme @frogtape #paintedaccentwall #accentwall
